ENUGU- Enugu State government on Thursday unveiled its plan to increase its Internally Generated Revenue (IGR) by 50 per cent in 2021. This was disclosed by the Commissioner for Budget and Planning, Mr. David Ugwunta, on Thursday a press briefing on the 2021 Appropriation Law of the state held at NUJ secretariat Enugu. According to him, such increase in IGR was one of the major objectives and targets of the 2021 budget. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The commissioner also said that the state would aim at upholding budget performance at not less than 85 per cent as well as maintain a capital expenditure to recurrent expenditure ratio of 60:40. Ugwunta said that the 2021 budget had key strategies that would improve on the current economic woes facing the state, the Nigerian economy and the world at large. Akpabio Calls For Partnership In Development Of Niger Delta Region Stop Derogatory Statements Against Minister Of Education, Makama Tells Bauchi APC He said, “This is considering the need to reflate the economy of the state and put Enugu on the path of economic recovery and growth.” “In order to actualize this thrust, Enugu State in 2021 has given full attention to complete all ongoing projects in 2020 financial year and initiate new projects and programmes with the 2021 budget”, he said.